job_post_list.description:
ByteDance will be prioritizing applicants who have a current right to work in Singapore, and do not require ByteDance's sponsorship of a visa.

About ByteDance
Founded in 2012, ByteDance's mission is to inspire creativity and enrich life. With a suite of more than a dozen products, including TikTok as well as platforms specific to the China market, including Toutiao, Douyin, and Xigua, ByteDance has made it easier and more fun for people to connect with, consume, and create content. 					

Why Join Us
Creation is the core of ByteDance's purpose. Our products are built to help imaginations thrive. This is doubly true of the teams that make our innovations possible.  Together, we inspire creativity and enrich life - a mission we aim towards achieving every day.  To us, every challenge, no matter how ambiguous, is an opportunity; to learn, to innovate, and to grow as one team. Status quo? Never. Courage? Always.  At ByteDance, we create together and grow together. That's how we drive impact-for ourselves, our company, and the users we serve.  Join us.				

About the Team
In the Organizational Culture (OC) department, our Internal Marketing and Engagement team (Global Event Hub) focuses on creating enriching activities and engagements for employees. We aim to raise awareness of our company's culture and mission, promoting global adoption of our values. Our goal is to foster teamwork, inspire passion at work, and unite everyone in achieving our objectives.

Responsibilities:
1. Responsible for planning and executing global culture campaigns and other culture experience projects in the APAC region, continuously optimize project execution to enhance employee experience;
2. For assigned projects, as a project manager, lead the project team members, as well as event partners and cross-functional teams from various regions, to drive project implementation and achieve related objectives;
3. Establish good relationships with stakeholders and collaborating teams in the APAC region, roll out collaboration&communication mechanisms, collect feedback from partners;
4. As a point of contact, responsible for coordinating with cross-functional teams in assigned countries/offices in the APAC region for daily consultation of employee culture experience and workplace culture environment;
5. Responsible for reviewing and approving internal applications for events, promotion channels, workplace culture assets within the APAC region. Communicate and coordinate with business partners to help them understand and apply relevant company guidelines.

